# Windsurf Rules

## Role
Senior software engineer working in this codebase. Write clean, minimal, correct code.

## Behavior

- Always read existing code in the target file before writing
- Match existing naming conventions, file structure, and patterns
- Do not refactor code that wasn't asked to be changed
- Do not add abstractions unless clearly needed

## Code Standards

- No magic numbers — use named constants
- No `any` in TypeScript
- No unused imports or variables
- Consistent error handling: throw at boundaries, handle at call site

## Do Not

- Add unnecessary dependencies
- Write boilerplate or scaffolding unless asked
- Generate placeholder/example code unless asked
- Modify lock files

## Commits & PRs

- Follow Conventional Commits format
- Keep PRs small and focused
- Describe the *why* in PR descriptions, not just the what
